    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @Kikobeats!\r\n\r\nThis guide shows an example of url sync with [react-router](https://github.com/ReactTraining/react-router) but it assumes it [has already been configured](https://github.com/ReactTraining/react-router#whats-it-look-like). If you did configure react-router, maybe you can share some code samples?\r\n\r\nAlso did you add the react-router dependency only to introduce the url synchronization? If you won't use react-router other features, maybe you can simply use another solutions.\r\nFor instance, on our examples I simply use [the browser history api](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/v2/docgen/src/examples/urlSync.js).\r\nAnother solution would be to use the [history library](https://github.com/mjackson/history). react-router uses it under the hood. \r\n\r\nAlso, maybe we should update the guide to make it clearer that it exists different solutions based on different needs.",
